-- Rauf Denktash Hospitalized in Critical Condition, Politis Says
-- B y   S t e l i o s   O r p h a n i d e s
-- 2012-01-13T09:23:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-13/rauf-denktash-hospitalized-in-critical-condition-politis-says.html
Former Turkish Cypriot leader Rauf Denktash is in the hospital in a critical condition,  Politis 
reported today citing his son Serdar Denktash.  Denktash, 87, served from 1983 until 2005 as president of
the breakaway Turkish Republic of  Northern Cyprus , which is
recognized only by  Turkey ; Politis said he is clear minded
although some of his vital organs are functioning irregularly.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stelios Orphanides in Nicosia at  sorphanides@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Craig Stirling at   cstirling1@bloomberg.net  